  "text": "K-ras. Mutations were searched throughout for the entire sequence of the gene. Screening of mutations in codons 12 and 13 was accomplished through mismatched primer-mediated PCR amplifications followed by restriction-fragment length polymorphism analysis using restriction endonucleases as already reported [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Mutated samples were then sequenced. Exon 2 of the K-ras gene was examined as follows: 200 ng of genomic DNA was amplified in 50 l of final volume reaction with 1ϫ PCR Buffer II; 1.5 mM MgCl 2 ; 0.2 mM dNTPs; and 0.5 M appropriate primer and 2 units of AmpliTaq. PCR amplifications were performed as follows: initial denaturation step of 96°C for 3 min; 45 cycles of 96°C for 30 s; 50°C for 1 min; 72°C for 1 min; and a final elongation step of 72°C for 4 min. The samples were run on 4% polyacrylamide gels and then sequenced.",
